This class describes a data field that is common to a group of Test Messages.
Such a common message therefore only makes sense where the Test Messages are
grouped together within Web Tests that share the context of the common field.

Such common fields are used to provide continuity between Test Messages
during the execution of each Web Test.  For example, many web-based
applications often require a "Session Id" that is issued upon the first
message request, and is then held as a data field within the HTTP query
string message.  For the web-application to make sense of any subsequent
message requests, the same Session Id must be sent with each request.

By setting up a Common Message Field, the Web Test will initialize the field
for he first Test Message, and will automatically retain its value to send
back for each subsequent Test Message.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="WebTest"/>
    <PrimAttribute name="defaultFieldValue" id="19f36ce8-5433-453c-aff3-e9c5a6d6eb49">
        <length>256</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="fieldName" id="c0c52e1f-3e67-4a1d-96b1-07cc199f9913">
        <length>61</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isValidateEqualTo" id="b0349106-9265-4230-b189-3b98c63ca66e">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>If this field is to be validated (ie. the returned value is to
be compared to the "defaultFieldValue"), then this flag will
be used thus:

	a)	If true, then the field value that is returned MUST be
		equal to the value of the "defaultFieldValue" property.

	b)	If false, then the field value that is returned MUST NOT be
		equal to the value of the "defaultFieldValue" property.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isValidateTagValue" id="fb57e028-9c62-4b94-b141-60ae4f9ab601">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>This flag indicates how the message field is to be treated (within
an internet query string). If true, then the field will be treated
as an HTML-type field, otherwise a normal query-string type field
will be assumed.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isValidatedField" id="88547137-b350-42fb-b79c-2da4f132accc">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>If this property is true, then the value that is returned in the Web Test message
response will be validated against the value of the "defaultFieldValue" property.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myWebTest" id="9a7ab2d4-5fba-4d5c-a75a-d7a2aeebf7c6">
        <kind>child</kind>
        <updateMode>manual</updateMode>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CnEcWebTest"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <Inverse name="CnEcWebTest::allCommonFields"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
    <JadeMethod name="getFieldType" id="c9fa2fbf-b8f5-47f2-bff2-59d5f8953a46">
        <source>getFieldType():String;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		08 June 2000 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Return the type of field for the receiver.
//
// Parameters:	None
//
// Returns:		The type of field.
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
begin
	if self.isValidateTagValue then
		return "HTML/XML Tag";
	else
		return "Query Field";
	endif;
end;</source>
        <ReturnType type="String"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="initializeMe" id="3b209650-2d7e-471b-a8ea-c26d2ad7e4e2">
        <updating/>
        <source>initializeMe(	pWebTest:CnEcWebTest;
				pFieldName:String;
				pDefaultValue:String;
				pIsValidatedField:Boolean;
				pIsValidateTagValue:Boolean;
				pIsValidateEqualTo:Boolean) updating;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		07 June 2000 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Initializes the receiver's property values.
//
// Parameters:	pWebTest - The owning web test object.
//				pFieldName - The name of the field.
//				pDefaultValue - The default field value.
//				pIsValidatedField - True if the field must be validated.
//				pIsValidateTagValue - True if the tag value must be validated.
//				pIsValudateEqualTo - True if validation check for equivalency.
//
// Returns:		Nothing
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
begin
	// Set the property values...

	self.defaultFieldValue	:=	pDefaultValue;
	self.isValidatedField	:=	pIsValidatedField;
	self.isValidateTagValue	:=	pIsValidateTagValue;
	self.isValidateEqualTo	:=	pIsValidateEqualTo;

	// Now set any key property values...

	self.fieldName			:=	pFieldName;

	// Last, set any references...

	self.myWebTest			:=	pWebTest;
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="pWebTest" type="CnEcWebTest"/>
        <Parameter name="pFieldName" type="String"/>
        <Parameter name="pDefaultValue" type="String"/>
        <Parameter name="pIsValidatedField" type="Boolean"/>
        <Parameter name="pIsValidateTagValue" type="Boolean"/>
        <Parameter name="pIsValidateEqualTo" type="Boolean"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="isFieldResponseValid" id="b2c9a6ad-43f7-4c1c-bde3-986248710166">
        <source>isFieldResponseValid(pFieldResponseValue:String):Boolean;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		07 June 2000 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Returnes a flag to indicated whether the passed response value is valid.
//
// Parameters:	pFieldResponseValue (String) - The field value that was returned to
//				the Web Test message request.
//
// Returns:		Boolean - If true, then the response is valid, otherwise it's not.
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
begin
	if (not self.isValidatedField) then
		// If the field doesn't require validation, then simply return a true value.
		return true;
	endif;

	if self.isValidateEqualTo and pFieldResponseValue = self.defaultFieldValue then
		return true;
	elseif (not self.isValidateEqualTo) and pFieldResponseValue &lt;&gt; self.defaultFieldValue then
		return true;
	else
		return false;
	endif;

	return false;
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="pFieldResponseValue" type="String"/>
        <ReturnType type="Boolean"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="updateMe" id="12b7d8d0-f49b-4048-a7c5-e59859c0efd0">
        <updating/>
        <source>updateMe(	pDefaultValue:String;
			pIsValidatedField:Boolean;
			pIsValidateTagValue:Boolean;
			pIsValidateEqualTo:Boolean) updating;
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Created:		07 June 2000 by cnwdad1
//
// Purpose:		Updates the receiver's property values.
//
// Parameters:	pDefaultValue - The default field value.
//				pIsValidatedField - True if the field must be validated.
//				pIsValidateTagValue - True if the tag value must be validated.
//				pIsValudateEqualTo - True if validation check for equivalency.
//
// Returns:		Nothing
//
// Changed On	Changed By	Reason
// ----------	----------	-------------------------------------------------------
//
// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
begin
	// Set the property values...

	self.defaultFieldValue	:=	pDefaultValue;
	self.isValidatedField	:=	pIsValidatedField;
	self.isValidateTagValue	:=	pIsValidateTagValue;
	self.isValidateEqualTo	:=	pIsValidateEqualTo;

	// Now set any key property values...

	// Last, set any references...
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="pDefaultValue" type="String"/>
        <Parameter name="pIsValidatedField" type="Boolean"/>
        <Parameter name="pIsValidateTagValue" type="Boolean"/>
        <Parameter name="pIsValidateEqualTo" type="Boolean"/>
    </JadeMethod>
</Class>
